  "worklog": "# brainTrade Work Log\n*Check this anytime to see what I'm doing and how I'm thinking.*\n\n## 2026-04-30 01:07 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 4] Fear edge stays real, but the first higher-sentiment decay zone needs monitoring before it earns a penalty\n\n**Task:** Re-test the Fear & Greed overlay with a cleaner state split, then harden the alpha pipeline so future P4 work can join sentiment to live microstructure/regime history instead of a single overwritten snapshot.\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive (`pm-bot`, `hl-bot`).\n- I matched the full `03h-shadow-sim-results.csv` sample (**1,168 trades across 20 dates**) to the full Alternative.me Fear & Greed history and wrote the artifact to `/home/ubuntu/clawd/research/p4-fear-greed-state-split-2026-04-30.md`.\n- The strongest pocket remains washed-out fear: with **abs_bias >= 50**, **yes_price 0.47-0.53**, and **persistence 3-16**, **F&G <= 15** printed **91.3% WR (103 trades)**.\n- The current conservative fear band **16-25** is still healthy at **86.5% WR (52 trades)**, so the existing fear-only positive overlay is still supported.\n- The first real degradation showed up above **40**: the same clean pocket dropped to **73.3% WR (15 trades)**, concentrated on **2026-04-23 (F&G 46)**. That is a meaningful warning, but still too small to justify a hard confidence penalty on its own.\n- I also upgraded the alpha pipeline in `scripts/alpha-signal-update.sh` so each hourly refresh now appends to **`research/alpha-signals-history.jsonl`** instead of only overwriting `research/alpha-signals.json`.\n\n**My thinking:** The earlier fear-side conclusion was right, but it was still too coarse. This pass says the real edge lives in washed-out fear plus already-clean execution context, while higher sentiment is a degradation watchlist rather than a production short-circuit. The pipeline change matters because P4 research was bottlenecked by having only one live alpha snapshot at a time.\n\n**Decision:** Keep the existing **fear-only boost** live, do **not** add a hard `>40` penalty yet, and start collecting hourly alpha history so the next P4 cycle can test sentiment together with live BTC breakout risk / regime state instead of sentiment alone.\n\n**Next:** On the next P1 heartbeat, rotate back to copy-intel per schedule. When P4 returns, use the new `alpha-signals-history.jsonl` archive to test whether higher-sentiment weak pockets only break when BTC microstructure is `active_trend` / `expanding`, or whether the decay is sentiment-led on its own.\n\n## 2026-04-29 21:08 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 3] Wallet-alignment guard exposed why the HL directional stack is still missing every setup\n\n**Task:** Audit the live HL directional engine against current funded capital, then turn the finding into an execution-quality guard instead of leaving the mismatch buried in logs.\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive (`pm-bot`, `hl-bot`).\n- The live Python HL engines are still executing against the old wallet **`0x51F290...3191`**, and that wallet currently has **$0.00**.\n",
